data.title: NJ election results 2023: State Senate, Assembly seats decided
data.meta_description: All 40 seats in the state Senate and the 80 seats in the state Assembly were on the line.
data.text:
Show Caption

Hide Caption

Legislative races to watch in New Jersey election: Video

Senior political writer Charles Stile breaks down specific races to watch, including a high-profile battle by the shore.

New Jersey voters headed to their local polling stations on Tuesday with the entire New Jersey Legislature up for grabs.

All 40 seats in the state Senate and the 80 seats in the state Assembly were on the line. All but two races were uncontested. General Assembly seats are two-year terms, while the Senate is four years.

In New Jersey, there are 6,494,988 registered voters for this general election, with 2,503,776 declared Democrats and 1,541,671 Republicans, according to the state Division of Elections website.

Here's a look at the unofficial results from the Associated Press in New Jersey's 40 districts for the Senate and Assembly (AP-declared winners in bold):
